We must look for transactions whose type is "Depreciation". In this data there are two such depreciation records:

• On 2024‑01‑01 there is a depreciation of 45,751.31  
• On 2024‑02‑01 there is a depreciation of 93,206.48

Before the period there is no accumulated depreciation so the initial accumulated depreciation is 0.00. Adding these two depreciation entries gives the ending accumulated depreciation:

  0.00 + 45,751.31 + 93,206.48 = 138,957.79

Thus, the accumulated depreciation item in the balance sheet has an initial value of 0.00 and an ending value of 138,957.79.
